&lt;p&gt;This position is a full-time, office-based position in Austin or Houston, TX and will be a member of the WhiteWater Supply Chain team. Responsibilities include drafting, amending, and reviewing contracts, managing service requests, and collaborating with suppliers and internal teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review, analyze, and manage supplier and vendor contracts to ensure compliance with company policies and procurement standards, including review of contract redlines, identification of contractual deviations and key issues, preparation of preliminary contract comments, and coordination of stakeholder review and negotiation responses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support department with contract creation using standard WhiteWater templates, preparing amendments, renewals and managing negotiations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with legal in determining risk assessment should amendments or non-standard terms arise&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor contract terms, pricing agreements, service-level agreements (SLAs), and delivery commitments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate contract updates, expiration timelines, and compliance requirements internally&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enter new and amended contracts into the applicable systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review invoices and purchase orders to verify alignment with contractual terms and pricing agreements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with suppliers and internal stakeholders to facilitate contract execution, administration, and issue resolution. Prepare contracts and contract summaries for review and execution by management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and audit contract management and vendor compliance systems to ensure data integrity, maintain required documentation, and monitor supplier compliance requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide assistance to internal stakeholders and vendors on contractual issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform routine and ad hoc reporting and analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify process improvement opportunities to enhance supply chain efficiency and contract administration workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Experience: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree preferred, or equivalent&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of direct Supply Chain experience coordinating contract renewals and amendments with procurement, legal, and supplier stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience reviewing contract redlines and preparing contract summaries preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High proficiency in MS Office Excel, Outlook, Word&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using Gatekeeper, NetSuite Enverus, OpenInvoice, &amp;nbsp;and Veriforce preferred&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated knowledge of workflow and business procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data analysis and reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent problem solving, time management, analytical and multi-tasking skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational skills with high attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to keep to assigned schedule&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communication and Teamwork skills required: Candidate must possess excellent interpersonal skills and effectively collaborate with others to optimize team success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;: This position is located in Austin or Houston, Texas.&amp;nbsp; Selected candidate is eligible for employer matched 401(k), medical, dental, vision, basic life and AD&amp;amp;D insurances and other benefit offerings.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Description:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This position is responsible for corrosion control and documentation for approximately 145 miles of pipe and associated compressor stations, assisting other Techs throughout Texas. This position will be based out of the Lake Charles, LA office and will be working from Lake Charles to Shreveport area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor both external and internal corrosion control and cathodic protection systems, perform maintenance and document accordingly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Asses pipeline conditions, recognize and prevent potential human or environmental threats and mitigate risk of safety incidents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Test and measure efficient operations of the cathodic protection systems and recommend corrosion prevention measures on pipeline facilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot areas of non-compliance, recommend corrective procedures and perform maintenance as needed including repairs and installations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct atmospheric and under insulation corrosion inspections, evaluate condition on pipeline coatings, and monitor data from the internal corrosion control system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review bids from 3&lt;sup&gt;rd&lt;/sup&gt; parties to make repairs and oversee/inspect work performed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document and maintain all records of system and facility evaluations, improvement recommendations and work performed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and document the scheduled regulatory inspections, including, but not limited to, rectifiers, bonds, AC mitigation and annual surveys&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate company standards, procedures and recordkeeping forms for WWM corrosion program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comply with safety, environmental and corrosion control regulations and company requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend safety trainings, maintain required certifications to perform job duties, set example of high safety standards and assist in regulatory inspections&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements &amp;amp; Qualifications: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma, or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 5 years of experience with corrosion control measures related to DOT 192 and Texas Railroad Commission&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with TRRC audits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must possess valid driver’s license and meet company insurability requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain compliance with WWM’s drug and alcohol program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Microsoft Office, various operating systems and perform basic math skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work overtime, weekends, holidays and respond to call outs and emergencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of reading and interpreting blueprints, PI&amp;amp;D&#39;s and other diagrams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge and experience in safe handling practices of flammable gases, liquid, and high/low pressure systems and follow Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) guidelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in changing climate conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work with a team, take direction from supervisors, keep required work schedules, focus attention on details, and follow work rules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills and fluency in English is required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to lift, push and pull a minimum of 75 lbs. and be able to work in tight spaces, climb to and work from elevated platforms, ladders, walkways, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is Full-Time located in Lake Charles, LA. Selected candidate is eligible for employer matched 401(k), medical, dental, vision, basic life and AD&amp;amp;D insurances and other benefit offerings.&lt;/p&gt;

