&lt;p&gt;Provide project management, technical support, and oversight for small-to-mid-sized capital projects ($1 MM – $10 MM). This role focuses primarily on natural gas meter stations and small-diameter lateral pipelines. As these projects are often reimbursable, the candidate must excel in transparent cost tracking, client communication, and efficient execution from inception to close-out.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full Lifecycle Management: Lead projects from initial scope development through construction, commissioning, and final asset integration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reimbursable Coordination: Maintain meticulous documentation for cost-plus or reimbursable projects to ensure seamless billing and client audit compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project Controls: Develop and maintain project schedules and budgets; generate accurate cost estimates and Authorizations for Expenditure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Specification: Perform sizing and specification for meter runs, valves, filters and piping components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Procurement &amp;amp; Bidding: Manage the material procurement process and lead the bidding/selection of third-party construction contractors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contract Management: Evaluate construction contracts and commercial agreements, ensuring scope clarity and risk mitigation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reporting: Lead weekly progress meetings and generate routine status reports for both internal personnel and external customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education: Minimum 4-year accredited degree in relevant discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: 2–3 years of experience with preference in midstream or utility industry experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project Scope: Direct experience with meter stations, interconnects, and/or small-diameter pipelines is highly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Client Facing: Ability to manage &quot;customer-driven&quot; projects where high levels of communication are required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Multi-Tasking: Proven ability to manage a portfolio of multiple smaller projects simultaneously at different stages of the lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Soft Skills: Self-motivated with a &quot;boots-on-the-ground&quot; mentality; comfortable working with both field technicians and executive leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Tools: Proficiency in MS Office (Project/Excel). Experience with AutoCAD or hydraulic modeling (e.g., ProMax, Synergi) is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel: Ability to travel approximately 25-50% to project sites for kick-offs, tie-ins, construction oversight, commissioning, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;: This position is located in Austin, Texas and is an in-office position.&amp;nbsp; Selected candidate is eligible for employer matched 401(k), medical, dental, vision, basic life and AD&amp;amp;D insurances and other benefit offerings.&lt;/p&gt;

